Intern and Batch Management System
1. Project Overview

The Intern and Batch Management System is designed to manage intern information and batch details within an organization. The system allows administrators to register interns, generate unique intern ID cards, create and manage batches, and track interns assigned to specific batches.

Each intern will be assigned a batch and will receive a unique ID based on their date of joining and ID card type. The system will also provide features for searching, updating, and managing intern records efficiently.

The application will be developed using Spring Boot for the backend and Angular for the frontend, with a relational database such as MySQL or PostgreSQL to store data.

2. Functional Requirements
2.1 Intern Management
2.1.1 Add Intern

The system should allow administrators to add a new intern by entering the following details:

Name (String)

Email (String)

Mobile Number (String)

ID Card Type (Free / Premium)

Date of Joining (Date)

Batch Assignment (Select from available batches)

Once the intern is registered, a unique Intern ID should be automatically generated.

2.1.2 Generate Intern ID

Each intern must have a unique ID generated automatically using the following format:

ID Card Type	Format
Free	TDA + DateOfJoining (YYYYMMDD) + Sequence Number
Premium	EMP + DateOfJoining (YYYYMMDD) + Sequence Number

Example IDs:

EMP20241129-001

TDA20241129-001

The sequence number must increment sequentially for each new intern.

2.1.3 Intern List

The system should display a list of all interns with the following details:

Intern ID

Name

Email

Mobile Number

Batch

ID Card Type

Date of Joining

This list will help administrators easily view and manage intern information.

2.2 Batch Management
2.2.1 Create Batch

Administrators should be able to create a new batch by entering the following details:

Start Date (Date)

The system should automatically calculate the End Date, which must be 6 months after the Start Date.

Example:

Start Date: 01 January 2024
End Date: 01 July 2024

2.2.2 Assign Interns to Batch

When registering a new intern, the system must require the administrator to assign the intern to an existing batch.

Each batch can contain multiple interns.

2.2.3 Batch List

The system should display a list of all batches including:

Batch Start Date

Batch End Date

Total Number of Interns

Intern Details (Name, ID Card Type, etc.)

This allows administrators to monitor batch activity and intern participation.

2.3 Additional Features
Update Intern Details

The system should allow administrators to update intern details such as:

Name

Email

Mobile Number

However, the Intern ID must remain unchanged once it is generated.

Delete Intern

The system should allow administrators to delete intern records when necessary.

Batch Overview

Each batch should provide an overview that includes:

Batch information

List of all assigned interns

Intern details such as name, ID card type, and joining date

Search and Filter

The system should support search and filtering capabilities based on:

Intern Name

Batch

ID Card Type

This will help administrators quickly locate specific intern records.

3. Non-Functional Requirements
3.1 Backend (Java – Spring Boot)
API Development

The backend should provide RESTful APIs to support the following operations:

Add a new intern

Generate an intern ID

Create batches

Assign interns to batches

Retrieve intern and batch details

These APIs will be used by the frontend application to interact with the database.

Database

A relational database such as MySQL or PostgreSQL will be used to store system data.

Two main tables will be created:

Intern Table

Batch Table

The tables will be connected through a foreign key relationship where each intern belongs to a batch.

ID Generation Logic

The system must implement a custom ID generation mechanism to ensure that:

Each intern receives a unique ID.

The ID follows the required format.

The sequence number increases correctly.

3.2 Frontend (Angular)
UI Components

The Angular application should include the following user interface components:

Intern Registration Form

Allows administrators to enter intern details

Provides batch selection

Batch Creation Form

Allows administrators to create a batch

Automatically calculates the end date

Intern List View

Displays all registered interns

Provides filtering options

Batch List View

Displays batch information

Shows the number of interns in each batch

Angular Material components such as tables, forms, and dropdown menus should be used to enhance the user interface.

Validation

The system should validate user inputs to ensure data accuracy.

Examples:

Email must follow a valid format

Mobile number must contain valid digits

Intern must be assigned to a batch before submission

Responsive Design

The frontend should be responsive so that the system can be used on:

Desktop

Tablet

Mobile devices

4. System Design
Batch End Date Calculation

The system automatically calculates the batch end date based on the start date.

Formula:

End Date = Start Date + 6 Months

ID Card Generation

Intern IDs are generated based on:

ID Card Type

Date of Joining

Sequential number

Examples:

EMP20241129-001
TDA20241129-002

This ensures that each intern has a unique identifier.

